title: RPITIT ICE when impl's fn is missing a type parameter

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
Found with a [modified fuzz-rustc](https://github.com/jruderman/fuzz-rustc) ### Code ```Rust #![feature(return_position_impl_trait_in_trait)] #[allow(incomplete_features)] struct S; trait Foo { fn bar() -> impl Sized; } impl Foo for S { fn bar() -> impl Sized {} } fn main() { S::bar(); } ``` ### Error output ``` error[E0049]: method `bar` has 0 type parameters but its trait declaration has 1 type parameter error: internal compiler error: compiler/rustc_middle/src/ty/subst.rs:726:9: type parameter `T/#1` (T/1) out of range when substituting, substs=[S] ```
